Land Transport Regulatory Authority (LATRA) has announced new transport fares for both daladala, regional and buses going to neighbouring countries to be effective from May 14, 2022. The Director General of LATRA, Mr Gilliard Ngewe made the announcement in Dar es Salaam on Saturday saying that for buses (daladala) that travel from 0-10 Kilometer the fare will 500/- instead of 400/- and the fare of 450/- will be 550/- which is an increase of 100/- Mr Ngewe added that for buses that travel 30 km the fare will be 850/- instead of 750/-, and for 35 km fare will be 1,000/- while for 40 km fare will be 1,100/- “As for buses going to the regions, standard class buses for one km the fare has increased by 11 per cent which is from 36/- to 41/- and as for the middle class it has increased by  6 per cent  from 53/- to 56.88/-,” LATRA director said Equally, he said that the new fares for buses traveling to the regions and neighbouring countries have increased by 11.92 per cent for standard class buses and for the middle class it has increased by 6.88 per cent.